{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1480358559,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxOTIwODQ3NjE=","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/20","origin":"github"},"title":"Add security tests","message":"There's still the myth of secure hash table functions around, esp. from the SipHash folks, as you can see at https://github.com/google/highwayhash/issues/28\nSo add tests to prove them otherwise.\n\n* brute-force collisions of the bit range 0-32, and present the timings and number of collisions.\n* use a solver for 10bits, and present the timings to find the collisions.\n\nAllow all keys of char 0-255, i.e. including null and control chars. hash functions take binary input, even if some applications reject those keys.\nIt is also a good metric for the hash function algorithmic complexity.","files":null}]}